Wrapper Classes
  data-type    wrapper class
* byte       - Byte
* short      - Short
* int        - Integer
* float      - Float
* long       - Long
* double     - Double
* char       - Character
* boolean    - Boolean


* Wrapper classes contains in-built methods which are used to perform
  basic operations on the primitive data types.
  
* wrapper classes are used to convert primitive values to java objects.

* For every primitive data type there is one corresponding wrapper class
  present in java.lang pkg. 
  
* If you try to assign a primitive value to an Object class ref. var then JVM
  1. Creates the object of that corresponding wrapper class.
  2. The address will be stored in Object class ref. var to perform upcasting.  

  
  